caption: The Best place in DC for Gin and Juice The Crab cake was Delicious.I love this Place
Restaurant looks beautiful and very clean from outside. I really wish they  keep their Ally and trash area clean also.

Worked with the manager Umbi to plan an event. He kept changing the price we had agreed on, charged my credit card more than what we agreed to in the end, and refuses to provide a receipt or return calls. I would encourage you to avoid doing business with this establishment.
Great food and drinks. Sat at the Gin Bar, Yaw the bartender was outstanding. Recommended some gins, was not disappointed.
A little pricey but the crabcakes and fried cauliflower were excellent.
The selection of gin is amazing, food is good
My food wasn't bad, some of the others seemed to have small portions.  Food prices were ok, but drink prices seemed a bit steep.  Definitely a relaxed atmosphere, as service was a bit lacking.

(Translated by Google) Friendly service, pleasant ambience, food is tasty, menu clearly arranged, but what is offered is good. Nice wine and beer offer. Pricing, as generally valid in the Washington area, higher than usual in the surrounding area.  (Original) Freundlicher Service, angenehmes Ambiente, Speisen schmackhaft, Speisekarte übersichtlich,  aber das, was angeboten wird, ist gut. Schönes Wein- und Bierangebot. Preislich, wie im Raum Washington allgemein gültig,  höher als im Umland üblich.

I had a drink and an appetizer at New Heights, thinking that it would be a nice experience. The experience soon turned out to be a nightmare. When I drank my water glass, there was a glass shard that came out and I almost swallowed it. Instead of expressing concern, the waitress just said that it wasn’t her fault and shrugged her shoulders.  I left the glass shard on the plate. it was a really dangerous situation that could’ve cut my throat or part of my gums. New Heights should train their employees to handle mishaps like these. Very disappointing experience.
Nice ambience!!!

Get the Gin flight. Great ambience. Great service. Everything was just great. I hope you enjoy this place as much as we did. I also recommend going upstairs unless it's a nice night to dine on the sidewalk.
Great food, a good place for a conversation with friends
Lovely dining room. Small menu that should be perfectly prepared.  So-so food.  Horribly slow service.  Had to ask for everything, including the menu.
Food was good, but service slow.

These guys are thieves -- they charged me for somebody else's meal. When I went up to them the manager said it was a fault with the till and that the money hadn't been taken out of my account. It was of course. My bank tried to dispute the transaction from the UK but they're now lying about the transaction. Don't go!
The food was good but a little pricey for what you get. Cocktails we're top notch.
Marvelous!!!
The service was great, but the food was mediocre for the price. Crab cake and mashed potatoes were delicious. Branzino and filet were relatively flavorless.

One of my favorite restaurants in the district! Make a reservation on OpenTable, and go early. I've eaten here twice, and both times got there between 6pm and 6:30pm. The downstairs is a bar, and it's always hopping. Go up the stairs, and find the restaurant space which is cozy, nice, and wonderfully quiet! The staff and owner take a personal interest in the guests, and you'll see quite a lot of people at your table. I appreciate this. It never feels intrusive. The food is good. Last time I was there, I didn't think it was as good as previous times, but it's still solid food. The menu changes, and the one online is never the one you get in the restaurant, but that doesn't bother me. They have a huge wine and cocktail list. Anything with gin is good. But, tell them what you're used to when it comes to drinks. They do experimental stuff, but they'll find something that fits your tastes.

Totally let down by the food when I went here. It was dead, with only maybe one other table sat, but the service was very slow. The food itself was pretty unappealing for everyone at the table. I had heard good things, so maybe it was an off night, but I don't plan on going back for the dining. I may go back to try the Gin Joint.
Amazing food, great service, and their gin fusions were fantastic. Shame the place is not more popular.
Great food and people.
Crazy delicious food. Service a little slow, but honestly worth it
Excellent good and ambience. Great gin selection
Food was great but a bit pricy.  Cocktail was good... lots of gin choices!!!
Tasty food. Little pricey, but worth it! Good for a date night.

Upstairs dining,, super delicious meeting our past experiences expecratstiins.? Downstairs bar, had horrible rap music and a bartender that was  a cool, non-welcoming, non-verbal, un-wine educated guy who eventually warmed up to us- we did all the work.  C- Asking him to change his music was laborious. We were one of two couples, almost same age -60’s in the bar.   Hey!!! Look around, it’s not that we don’t appreciate the music de jour, it’s just appalling when you’re being bombarded with pounding, awlful lyrics at 4:30 - 5 happy hour!  I asked him to change the pounding rap, but was told it was a play list.   Hmmm... so we spent $50+ 20% tip ( We owned a restaurant).  Upstairs was a joyful, absolutely delightful experience!  Food was exceptional, as was service and the GM in charge. A remarkably engaging man whom we recalled from our earlier visits.  We live close by on Kalorama Rd. Suggestion:  Have upstairs Re-train your bartender to be more welcoming and wine knowledgeable. He is attractive and knows his gin, but takes waaay toooo long to be pleasant and welcoming!  And check out his play list!!! How about Begin with Tony Bennet and Amy or geez just about anyone other than bam, bam, bam loud music  it’s about looking around and seeing who your customers are.   Not that hard!! I won’t come back or recommend until you stand out! Way too much competition!!!
Best gin joint in DC.  If you are a gin lover, there's no better selection in the city. Talented chef. Hokkaido scallops were beyond excellent. Presentation was fantabulous.
Excellent!!!
Food was amazing, drinks were great.  10 for 10, would dine again.
Awesome food, drinks, and atmosphere. Service was slow though.

Great food and service.  Went there with about eight other folks from a convention.  Service was very friendly and attentive without being overbearing.  The waiter was easily able to provide individual checks for everyone so they could use the receipts for their expense account reporting.
Food and service are excellent! I hope to go back the someday.
Everything was just ok. Not worth the price tag on these dishes. Flavors are muddled. My $100 dinner should have been no more than $45 top.

The service was awful, minus the folks bussing and filling water. It took 40 minutes to even have a drink order taken, then another 20 before we ordered food. The price fixe menu started out positively with a delicious sweet potato soup but went down from there with tough, dry duck (how do you even make duck tough and dry??) and mediocre “deconstructed” apple pie.
We went with a group and somehow after ordering a  salad, a side and sharing a bottle of wine, my bill came to $55. My friend's ravioli arrived frozen and they didn't seem to care.
Great food, excellent service, quiet atmosphere conducive for good conversation with friends. Very nice.

Under no circumstances would I go to this restaurant again.  Last night there were only two parties in the restaurant, ours and a party consisting of an adult male and five young women ranging in age between approximately 18 and 24.  The women were literally screaming at the top of their lungs, making my party impossible to converse.  I complained to the manager, who defended them and stated they were just being "festive."  I responded that their loud screaming was inhibiting our ability to converse.  I asked the manager to speak to them; he refused and proceeded to provide all sorts of excuses for their uncivil behavior ("once their food comes, they'll quiet down").  Finally, I had had it and went to the table and asked the women to stop screaming.  One gave me a snarky remark.  They continued screaming throughout their stay.  The management didn't even offer to move my party, despite the fact that there were plenty of empty tables in the restaurant.  This is an expensive restaurant for food that is just OK.  This situation speaks volumes about where America is today.  People are becoming more and more uncivil and disrespectful of people around them.  Extreme individualism and political correctness (everyone is right, and no one should be confronted when he/she engages in behavior which disrespects the people in the vicinity).  I will never go to this restaurant again.
Truly  a hidden gem. Terrific, interesting food, and the prices are modest by D.C. standards.  It to be missed.
If you love gin, this is for you.
Good food. Strategic location

What a warm-hearted place. I needed some help with my car and the  very kind  manager jumped out from tending a very crowded bar to lend assistance. Then followed a friendly, knowledgable and  and cheerful waiter who served beautifully prepared and delicious food. My steak was like "butter," and all others at our table where happy with their preparations.  One reviewer called this venue "civilized" and I second that description. No pretense, just lots of sincerity and great food.
I had the duck croquettes to start and scallops on spinach risotto for main dish, with the pan pardue for dessert, and everything was amazing.

We arrived for a 7:45 reservation and did not get our food until 9:15.  We asked for some accommodation and the offer was dessert--not a positive response given that we had an early morning meeting.  Although the food was good--not spectacular--the service was horrible.  And, it was Sunday night and half the restaurant was empty.  I can't imagine how long one would have to wait if the tables were all full.

Attractive place one block from a Metro station and near two major convention hotels. Trendy "new American" cuisine very nicely prepared and gracefully served. Very accommodating of food allergies. Lots of appetizers and entrees dairy and egg-free.
This was the absolute best date night I ever had. I fell in love here. The food was delicious and the gin drinks were to die for. I hope to be back one day.
Temperature was way too hot in the dining room. Steak had a strong burnt taste. Good service.
Amazing gin selection and fantastic house made tonics

This was some seriously delicious food and cocktails! Who knew there were so many kinds of gin? I had wine I'd never even heard of before! What a unique and enjoyable adventure! And I love sitting outdoors :)

Fantastic food and knowledgeable bar staff, they helped guide me through the impressive list of gins and house-made tonics. I highly recommend the monkey 47 gin. The bronzino was cooked to perfection and the décor was upscale. I will be certain to return on my next trip to DC.

This place is a sleeper. We've only been here twice but both times we very surprised by the quality of our meals. For me, it was the scallops that really won me over. I love scallops, but rarely order them while dining out because even good restaurants so often screw them up.  Here, they were excellent. The fish and lettuce wraps have also proven to be delicious. I get it: this place doesn't look like much from the outside, the decor a little boring, the neighborhood isn't known for having high quality restaurants, and I'm not sure the owners are as attuned to cultivating their reputation as they should be; I don't think anyone walks into N.H. and feels like they're entering a top DC restaurant, there is no detectable "buzz." But I've got to say, for a neighborhood place, it hits way above its weight -- some of the better meals I've had anywhere in town (and the service is good too).
This place tries hard, but on delivery, it's just OK. I got the scallops for dinner and they were overcooked.
Great place

Service was incredibly slow, portions were small and too expensive for what you got. Do not bring others if you intend to split the check, they don't know what that is or how to do it. You'll be stuck there forever so don't plan anything afterwards!
the service was good and the decour is nice but the food was not good. the salad was extremely salty and the stake was simply bland and boring.
Interesting drinks, great service, but uninspired and expensive fare.
Wonderful food, service and atmosphere. One of the best restaurants in the city.

A hidden gem in Woodley Park. New Heights has awesome food although I'm never really impressed with the desserts which lean towards molecular gastronomy. I love the Gin Joint Bar downstairs. Nicole, the bartender, is simply amazing and creates custom drinks with her own housemade, infused tonics. I like to go and treat it like a speakeasy. With her knowledge of gins and all spirits, I always have a new cocktail to try and experience a new flavor combination.
Went on a Monday night. Servers were very attentive and food was delicous.

Good service & good food. Soup was super, but not hot. Portions are SMALL, but food was excellent. Gin was excellent, but Gin Joint downstairs was too small & crowded to even get into so we had the drinks upstairs at our table before dinner. All high end restaurants I have ever been in serve 4 scallops for the meal portion; they only served 3 - for twenty some dollars! They did not refresh(refill) our cups of coffee-I have not ever had that happen at upscale restaurant. Still, it was a very good meal & we all enjoyed it.

Gave us the best seat in the dining room. This was about the best part...  Waiter didn't tell us the specials. Didn't tell us what wasn't on the menu that night. Apparently there are also three menus for this restaurant depending if you're at the bar, patio, or upstairs, which is ABSURD...so what I'd seen online wasn't the same.  Waiter took our order, forgot our bread (we had to ask for it too) and when it came, it wasn't even warm. Received my cocktail after ten minutes, the waiter handed us a random "from the chef" veggie and creme fraiche thing on spoons that we hated when we looked distraught. The people who refilled water and bused tables were the most responsive people. If only we could have tipped their attentiveness instead...  Food did come. I had the lamb, mother had chicken, father steak. Food cooked to perfection, which is a saving grace, but the annoyance was the wait staff, not the actual food. Fingerling potatoes were great.  Perhaps this is just one problem with one waiter, but it's enough to stop you from wanting to go back for a $200+ meal for three, right? I'd rather go to Palena.
amazing food, extremely passionate chef, service impecable, great gin cocktails!
Came for the gin. Stayed for the hangover!
Good food, good gin
excellent
simply marvelous.
